#Topic ##
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
#Topic Text Direction

Skia draws text as a series of glyphs, but does not implement font substitution, 
textual substitution, line layout, or contextual spacing like kerning pairs. Use
a text shaping engine like #A HarfBuzz #http://harfbuzz.org/ ## to translate text runs
into glyph series.

Text Direction selects whether text is drawn left to right or top to bottom.

Flags kVerticalText_Flag if clear draws text left to right.
Flags kVerticalText_Flag if set draws text top to bottom.

Text Direction is left to right by default.
Text Direction can be defaulted to top to bottom by setting SkPaintDefaults_Flags to
kVerticalText_Flag at compile time.

#Example

void draw(SkCanvas* canvas) {
    SkPaint paint;
    paint.setAntiAlias(true);
    paint.setTextSize(50);
    for (bool vertical : { false, true } ) {
        paint.setVerticalText(vertical);
        canvas->drawText("aAlL", 4, 25, 50, p);
    }
}

#Example ##

