#Topic ##
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
#Topic Underline and Strikethrough

Underline and Strikethrough draw lines in the paint color over the text.

Underline and Strikethrough do not use Paint Font Metrics
to compute the lines' position or thickness.

The line width is computed by measureText, and the line height is the setTextSize / 18.
Underline is offset below the baseline by setTextSize / 9, and StrikeThrough is offset
above the baseline by setTextSize * 2 / 7.

Implement a custom font style by retrieving Paint Font Metrics and using Path Effect.
Use Text Intercepts to construct a line that skips over text strokes.

Flags kUnderlineText_Flag draws underlined text if set.
Flags kStrikeThruText_Flag text with strikethrough if set.

Underline and Strikethrough are disabled by default.

#Example
void draw(SkCanvas* canvas) {
    SkPaint paint;
    paint.setAntiAlias(true);
    paint.setTextSize(40);
    paint.setUnderlineText(true);
    paint.setStrikeThruText(true);
    canvas->drawText("OjYy_-", 6, 10, 50, paint);
}
#Example ##

