#Method SkScalar measureText(const void* text, size_t length, SkRect* bounds) const

Return a rectangle that represents the union of the bounds of all
of the glyphs, but each one positioned at (0,0). This may be conservatively large, and
will not take into account any hinting, but will respect any text-scale-x or text-skew-x
on this paint.


#Example
    SkPaint paint;
    SkDebugf("default width = %g\n", paint.measureText("!", 1));
    paint.setTextSize(paint.getTextSize() * 2);
    SkDebugf("double width = %g\n", paint.measureText("!", 1));

    #StdOut #measureText
    default width = 3
    double width = 7
    #StdOut ##
